DialogueLine.dialogue: I've checked the storage unit just now and... one of the new artifacts went missing.
Anyway, since I just got here, I checked on the artifacts for the next exhibition. One of the new ones went missing.
Hey, Jonathan. How's your weekend?
Ah, right! I hope you're still able to rest though.
I was just hoping to become friendlier with you. We work together, after all.
Hm. Okay, suit yourself.
I don't know, I just got here. Do you have any idea?
That's what I'm here to ask you. You *were* guarding the museum, yes?
I was hoping you've seen something suspicious.
Okay, so Cassandra was in the museum too. Do you think she saw anything?
And what were you doing at the time?
Where were you?
Where do you think it could have gone?
And you're just telling me this now because?
How did you know she never came out?
What?
You're sure you were watching the *entire* night?
If she never left the storage unit, I'd see her there, though...
You're sure you weren't dreaming, then?
Can you describe her a bit more?
Your description of her is pretty vague. What about what she looks like?
I can't really say that your description of her is particularly helpful.
Have you seen Director Virgil anywhere?
Where's Director Virgil?
Did the director drop by today?
Let me call him.
Have you seen her enter the storage unit?
It's possible she could have stolen the plinth, then.
If you haven't seen her come out, then don't you think Cassandra stole the plinth?
If you've been too busy watching the cameras, then Cassandra definitely stole the plinth.
Jonathan thinks you stole the plinth. So do I.
Jonathan thinks you stole the plinth.
Did you steal the plinth?
The plinth went missing.
The plinth went missing. Do you know anything about it?
Hi, Cass. How did your weekend go?
I've got bad news, Cass. The plinth is gone.
When did you last see it?
What were you doing last night?
Did you see anything strange last night?
Hey Cass. How're you? You look... tired.
Jonathan, Cassandra told me you dropped by the night before. Is that true?
I just talked to Cassandra. She told me you were asking about the plinth.
Care to explain why you were asking about the plinth? Cassandra told me.
Do you have any ideas where the artifact went?
If it isn't Jonathan's doing, what do you think happened?
What about your cut? What happened?
I heard you got a bad cut. Are you okay?
Was there anything suspicious about her?
What was she doing then?
Jonathan told me he visited you to check if you were going to work overtime. Is this true?
I want to ask about the broken cabinet.
I want to ask about the broken cabinet in storage.
I checked the broken cabinet. It's sharp. That's where you got cut?
That was when you got the cut?
After that, you didn't touch or move the plinth?
Where did you last see it?
Why?
So it's true?
I'm sorry I put you on the spot. Just explain why you were asking about it, please.
Are you really upset about that? ... Why?
I wasn't asking for your opinion.
Okay. I'll make note of that.
